replies.body:
They're reworking one trick ponies and adding hugely diverse Champions.

The old Fiora just autos and ultis - that's her whole life story.

The old Garen just Q's and E's then walks away then Q's and E's then walks away then Q's and E's then R's.

Darius just ran around mashing Q on people then tried to grab them or get stacks on them and ulti them;

They added Diversity to these Champions;

Poppy has so much in her kit it's beyond a Joke - Damage >10% current health reduced by 50% - Invulnerability to 4 Champions and their CC's plus % bonus damage, AD and AP scaling; % Current HP damage, a stun, a dash; Stat boost on autos or instantly boosted and a move speed steroid - all in all a ridiculously hard Champion to balance hence they have given her like 1 Stat change since her release despite her falling out of favour and probably did so to look at her kit as a whole later in a diverse update that puts her in a good spot, rather than a few nerfs/buffs or w/e that will lead to her being a monster again or will fail to tackle the correct issue which is making her a 50-50 Champion.

Yorick is similary hard to balance because his power spikes are all over the place which is why he too was just nerfed shortly after release and left because he needs a thorough update and Urgot is similarly hard to balance because of how diverse he is so all in all 2 of them (Poppy and Urgot) were left because of how diverse they are and hence hard to balance and the other has power spikes all over the place and I'm pretty sure - seeing as the majority of what Riot does is add interest and diversity to the League - they would rather leave a Champion intact and put them on a priority 3 and add new Champions with a priority 8;

All 3 of them are still playable although Urgot and Yorick aren't quite as good as they used to be and Poppy is difficult to play but can still perform reasonably well - because they are still "entities" and have so much diversity and are still played and adding interest is Riots #1 priority - adding content creates for a more fun game than simply balancing does - because that's literally what a rework to a Champion is- a balance change; while adding a bit of diversity - and a more Chaotic game is better than a simple click war - the more diversity, the more randomness, learning, chaos and fun the game is - while balancing is keeping it under wraps so things aren't chaoticly ordered where power figures rise to monstrous levels and to keep it chaotic and always keep you in new and interesting situations new Champs are added and as a less important priority to Riot IMO - Champions that have fallen off in a lot of ways are updated but keep to their style to some extent while being made more chaotic so as to be floated back to that 50% mark eventually and as the game tumbles forwards keeping fresh and new, the outliers that fall behind are given a bump back up every so often so that while it is constantly new and Changing; there are still familiar faces on the frontlines of the struggle for runeterran glory.
